info.title: BioStar 2 API
info.description:
HTTP Header 'Content-Language' is used for language.  ISO-639-1, ISO-639-3 values are supported.
 Response.coe reference: C:\Program Files\BioStar 2(x64)\nginx\html\resources\messages_en.properties(ACB_ERROR_CODE.XXXXX)
When testing API in Swagger, special characters cannot be used in URL parameters due to encoding issues.

This document is not being maintained. For the latest documentation, see the following link:
 https://bs2api.biostar2.com/

name.description: desc: Input Access Group Name to Create

user_sync_method.description:
desc: Automatic User Synchromization 
 [Not Used : (user_sync_method : "0" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")] 
 [All Devices : (user_sync_method : "1" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")] 
 [All Devices(Including user update from device) : (user_sync_method : "1" & user_by_device_sync_method:"1")] 
 [Specific Devices(Only devices belonging to the access group) : (user_sync_method : "3" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")]

user_by_device_sync_method.description:
desc: Automatic User Synchromization 
 [Not Used : (user_sync_method : "0" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")] 
 [All Devices : (user_sync_method : "1" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")] 
 [All Devices(Including user update from device) : (user_sync_method : "1" & user_by_device_sync_method:"1")] 
 [Specific Devices(Only devices belonging to the access group) : (user_sync_method : "3" & user_by_device_sync_method:"0")]

Not Use : 0
